## Authentication

Each service account uses **key-pair authentication** (RSA). You will need to:

1. Generate an RSA key pair for each service account
2. Set the public key on the user object
3. Store the private key in your secrets manager

```bash
# Generate key pair per service account
openssl genrsa 2048 | openssl pkcs8 -topk8 -inform PEM -out rsa_key.p8 -nocrypt
openssl rsa -in rsa_key.p8 -pubout -out rsa_key.pub
```

## Post-Creation Checklist

For each service account:
- [ ] RSA public key set on user object
- [ ] Private key stored in secrets manager
- [ ] Connection tested with key-pair auth
- [ ] Default role activates automatically
- [ ] Default warehouse is used
- [ ] Service account cannot access objects outside its role

